Sr. sence my last to you on the 30 patt. yd of 10 ditto I am gladd you were
no disapointed in the bill of Â£73:10:18- though my freind here is an
able & vere good man: ichd. pindar is well arrived att brugges for which
thanck godd I know not yett what goods you shipt on his board, butt
that I shall know to norrow from brugges, the goods come vere
seasonable what is yett be hinde will all doubtlees be ready for the first
ship att Hull: I desire you to in order pr. first 20 bayes of 40 a 40 &
weight of 50 a 52 a p. as formerly wee hadd besides 12 peeces of
the A.H.S ggeen head aswere under the last parcell & lett of
them 32:p be made one Bale & dispatiiee with all expedition
our trade beginnes to come on, so hope to be in condition to guix
you the necessary suplyes with mons whilst now Iremaine
